description:
Final Volume!

In this astonishing series conclusion, Azuma and team Pantasia face off against a longtime enemy deep in the forests of Mount Fuji. Azuma's bread-making acumen, Kanmuri's quick thinking and Kawachi's unexpected martial arts abilities may not be enough to counter their cosmically crusty foe. Moreover, global warming caused by all that baking threatens to make toast out of Azuma's dream of creating the perfect Ja-pan! Can bread really save the world? Find out in the final volume of Yakitate!! Japan!

Chapter Titles

  • Story 232: Evolution of Kirisaki
  • Story 233: Kawachi's Fault
  • Story 234: Ja-pan = Sandwich Pan?
  • Story 235: A Famous Composer
  • Story 236: Spirit
  • Story 237: Happy Days
  • Story 238: The Sinking Country
  • Story 239: Dedication, Strength and Compassion
  • Story 240: Kuroyanagi's Plot
  • Story 241: That Is the Maldives...
  • Final Story: What Do You Mean?!

description:
Robur and his allies have now joined the secret base of the resistance, located on the icy shores of Antarctica at the secret ancient city Atlante built there 20,000 years by mysterious aliens, the legendary Atlantis. This is where scholars of the resistance prepare a secret weapon against attack: the "Gabriel Project".

But the invading Selenites are not standing still either. In the first album, Queen Selene recognized the Mark "Logoi" in the spirit of Robur.

The Logoi are prodigious alien world manufacturers, which in the distant past invaded Earth and taught some of their enigmatic science to Atlantis. The Selenites, to survive, must at all costs capture Robur and force him to confess the secrets he holds. Robur's new opponent is Zylber Doc, the "Platinum Man" a prototypical Nazi superman, sent by the Roman Empire of the "Ubermensch".

Zylber is an ally of the Selenites and he venerates as the "Master Race", destined to dominate the universe.

Zylber, Gurn and Josephine Balsamo are at the head of a German armada consisting of strange machines, and launch a massive attack on the polar city defended by Robur.

Can Robur save Atlantis?
name: Robur: 20,000 Ans Sous les Mers

description:
1933 - the Earth is still under the domination of the Nazi's alien allies the Selenites

The attack against the Earth's resistance forces is organized at the strange "Red Base" hidden in the Hoggar Mountains.

At the head of a vast interplanetary armada, Robur, Gayle and the rest of the team's mission is to reach the center of the Moon, find the "Matrix" Queen Selene, and destroy the "gravitational engines" of the Selenites who have the power to project the Moon on the Earth!

But inconceivable dangers threaten our heroes during the route that will take the heart of our satellite. In the shadows, a Nazi "mole" has infiltrated team Robur and informs the mysterious Selenites.

The curtain opens on the last act ... relations between Gayle and Robur become complicated and the mysterious origins of Robur will finally be revealed ...
